place.name: CROSTWIGHT
place.gazetteerText: CROSTWIGHT, a parish in Tunstead district, Norfolk; 3½ miles E by S of North Walsham railway station, and 16 NE by N of Norwich. Post town, North Walsham, under-Norwich. Acres, 777. Real property, £1, 243. Pop., 73. Houses, 15. The property is divided between two. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £66.* Patron, M. Shephard. Esq. The church is old but good, and has a tower. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
